title: Alabama/Texas A&M Set for 2:30 p.m. on CBS
text:
By Alabama News Network 
Story Created: Oct 5, 2015 at 2:18 PM CDT TUSCALOOSA, Ala. – The Southeastern Conference announced Monday that Alabama’s game at No. 9 Texas A&M on Saturday, October 17, will kick off at 2:30 p.m. (CT) and will be televised nationally on CBS.Get all the latest information on the team by following @AlabamaFTBL on Twitter and Facebook and AlabamaFBL on Instagram. General athletic news can also be found at UA_Athletics on Twitter and Instagram and AlabamaAthletics on Facebook.SEC Television Schedule for Saturday, October 10, 2015Louisiana Tech at Mississippi State, 11 a.m. CT on SEC NetworkOle Miss at Memphis, 11 a.m. CT on ABCAlabama at Texas A&M, 2:30 p.m. CT on CBSVanderbilt at South Carolina, 3 p.m. CT on SEC NetworkFlorida at LSU, 6 p.m. CT on ESPNMissouri at Georgia, 6:30 p.m. CT on SEC Network
